  "article": "In a remarkable display of open-source ingenuity, a developer has taken matters into their own hands and built a custom WiFi driver for their older MacBook running the FreeBSD operating system. FreeBSD, a free and open-source Unix-like operating system, is known for its stability and security, but it often lags behind in hardware support compared to more mainstream operating systems like Windows and macOS.

