Additionally, the rise of low-code and no-code platforms has democratized software development, enabling non-technical users to create sophisticated applications with minimal coding expertise. These tools empower businesses to rapidly prototype and deploy new solutions, accelerating the pace of innovation.

The declining cost of writing code also has implications for the job market. As the barrier to entry for software development decreases, more individuals are gaining the skills and confidence to contribute to the tech industry. This influx of talent is driving increased competition and potentially leading to a shift in the traditional career paths within the sector.

